en_62885_0	The Commander, Security Forces - East (SF-E), Major General Santhusitha Pananwala laid the foundation stone for construction of the new Stupa at the Buddhist Centre Welikanda, amidst chanting of ‘Seth Pirith’ by members of the Maha Sangha on Tuesday (26).
en_62885_1	The event was held under the guidance of the Chief Incumbent Buddhist Centre Welikanda, Ven.
en_62885_2	Delwita Mettalankara Thero.
en_62885_3	Colonel General Staff SFHQ-E, Colonel Chaminda Wijayaratne and several Senior Officers participated in the project.
en_62885_4	This temple was established in 1942 and survived during the conflict with many difficulties.
en_62885_5	The temple lacked this object of veneration, the Pagoda (Stupa), one of the main features in typical places of Buddhist worship.
en_62885_6	With the generosity of Mr. Saddhathissa in Kelaniya area, the construction of this ‘Stupa’ is to be completed within a few months.
en_62885_7	A gathering of Buddhist devotees took part in the ceremony.
